SITUATION: 41-year-old G3P2 at 41+5 weeks gestation requiring assessment for post-term pregnancy management

BACKGROUND: Mrs Kowalski is now 5 days past her expected delivery date based on accurate dating from early pregnancy scan at 8 weeks. She has experienced irregular Braxton Hicks contractions but no established labor. Baby movements remain good but she reports they feel different - less frequent rolling movements, more sharp jabs.
